<TITLE> 7 killed, dozens injured in road accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 10 (bdnews24.com) -- At least seven were killed and 56 injured in four road accidents at Lakshmipur, Rangpur, Chapainawabganj and Savar. Lakshmipur bdnews24.com's Lakshmipur correspondent reported that a bus fell into a roadside ditch at Kamalnagar Upazila at Monday dawn killing four and injuring nearly 50 passengers. Two of the dead were identified as Kishor Chandra, 26, from Dakkhin Charapur village of the sadar upazila and Kabir Hosain, 25, from Balur Char village of Lalmohan Upazila of Bhola. The injured were admitted at Kamalnagar and Rangati upazila health complex and at Lakshmipur Sadar hospital. Police said most of the injured are from Bhola and Barisal. An injured passenger Masud told bdnews24.com that the bus assistant had taken the place of the driver who had left the bus at Lakshmipur. The assistant lost control near Millat Academy. The bus was coming from Chittagong, he said. Deputy commissioner and police super of Lakshmipur visited the scene. Rangpur bdnews24.com's Rangpur correspondent reported that an SSC examinee named Renu Begum, 16, was killed when a speeding truck hit her rickshaw at the city's Textile crossing. SI Chandan Kumar, in charge of Dhap police camp said, "Renu died on spot. Her mother, Sufia, was injured also." The police managed to capture the truck, however, its driver escaped, the police official said. Chapainawabganj bdnews24.com correspondent reports that a woman called Rokhsana was run over by a speeding Rajshahi-bound truck at the city's Dariarpur area. Sub-inspector of Rajshahi police Saiful Islam told bdnews24.com that Rokhsana died on the spot and that a case for has been filed at the Sadar Police Station. Savar bdnews24.com correspondent reported that one died and four others were injured in a head-on collision between a bus and a tempu (three-wheel human hauler) in Savar. The situation of the two injured people is critical and they are receiving treatment at a local hospital. The accident took place at the C&B area on the Dhaka-Aricha highway around 11am. The identity of the dead could not be ascertained immediately. Abu Taher, sub-inspector of Savar Police said that a Dhaka-bound bus hit a tempu. The tempu driver died on the spot and four passengers were injured, he added. The police are trying to find the bus and it's driver. bdnews
